{
  "text": "It has been reported that HIV-1 entry into human intestinal epithelial cell lines can be blocked by either anti-GalCer or anti-CXCR4 mAbs, suggesting that CXCR4 can cooperate with GalCer during the fusion process [CITATION_1] . We assessed the migration of Cgt \u00ff/\u00ff BM mononuclear cells toward CXCL12 to investigate whether the mobilization defect arose from CXCR4 dysfunction on Cgt \u00ff/\u00ff hematopoietic cells. However, Cgt \u00ff/\u00ff and +/+ cells did not differ in CXCL12-mediated migration ( Figure 1E ). To evaluate further whether the defect in HSPC mobilization observed in Cgt \u00ff/\u00ff mice could originate from hematopoietic cells, Cgt +/+ or \u00ff/\u00ff BM nucleated cells (BMNCs;",
